We have seen evidence on the Giza​ Plateau of scorch marks which are in places where the sun would have been focused onto the ground from the strong reflecting heat of the sun off the polished limestone casing blocks. This lead us to surmise that the bowls gathered at Abu Ghorab, which seem to have been used elsewhere to be brought to Abu Ghorab, could have been placed to reflect the heat of the sun to specific places for heating and cutting blocks, for instance. Just as a solar oven can be moved to be set up in different places. It's a theory that made sense to us so we are sharing it for what it's worth.

Credit https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=x38ivoXpsf0&feature=youtu.be

node.text:
If not given drugs to prevent infant death, the pregnant body of a rhesus negative mother will attack, try to reject, and even kill her own offspring if it is by a rhesus positive man.

The Domestic dog (Canis lupus familiaris) is a sub-species of the gray wolf (Canis lupus), and they produce hybrids. There are numerous other examples of where two separate species (for example with different numbers of chromosomes) can also produce viable offspring, yet are considered separate species. That said, humanity has been shown to be, genetically speaking, a hybrid species that did not all share the same ancestry in Africa.

Recent sequencing of ancient genomes suggests that cross-species interracial interbreeding went on between the members of several human-like groups more than 30,000 years ago, including an as-yet unknown human ancestor. "There were many hominid populations,” says Mark Thomas, evolutionary geneticist at University College London.

Some Interesting Similarities.
The fascinating thing is that most of our apomorphic characteristics are shared with marine mammals. There are physiological traits that humans and dolphins share that chimps, monkeys and gorillas do not. In fact, these characteristics are completely lacking in most land mammals.

If we look at the characteristics that we share with dolphins and do not share with chimpanzees, we find conscious breath control, greatly reduced body hair, subcutaneous body fat, and greater brain size and complexity. Dolphins, however, became fully aquatic, whereas humans evolved to be semi aquatic.

Sound vibrations forming geometric patterns in sound resonance (Cymatics) experiment. #scienceismagic Vibration rearranges matter. This is the power of the influence of sound vibrations in matter.

Different frequencies creates different patterns. These patterns are repeatable, not random.

Cymatics has been called "Chladni Figures", they are shapes that appear on surfaces when they vibrate at certain frequencies.

Ernst Chladni (1756—1827), considered the founder of acoustics, discovered that when we vibrate a metal plate with an object, such as a stick or a violin bow, for example, it forms geometric shapes. When scattering grains of sand on the metal surface, it agitates over the plate, accumulating in some points (nodes), in which the plate is not vibrating. This accumulation produces the patterns observed in the video.

The plates have numerous possibilities for vibration, each corresponding to a specific frequency of the sound. Each vibration produces a unique pattern, and the complexity of the designs also increases with the vibration. In addition, depending on where the surface is affixed, its size, the material with which it is composed and its thickness, vibrations will occur at certain frequencies.

The nature of these phenomena leads us to inquire about the vibratory forces that act in the structuring of nature's processes and forms. We are led, by analogies, to visualize the world as a great interweaving of vibrations and harmonies, consonant and dissonant, structuring and dissolving the substances in cycles of chaos and order governed by an invisible geometric matrix of vibration.

Scene from "Inner Worlds, Outer Worlds" by Dan Schmidt.

A Maya book is referred to as a codex. The codices were painted onto a paper made of bark from the fig tree and folded out like an accordion.

node.text: Other Homo sapiens specific features that may be tied to a semi-aquatic stage of human evolution include erect posture, loss of body hair, deposition of subcutaneous fat, a completely different heat-regulation system from other primates, and kidneys that function much like those of aquatic mammals.

That is fact. It is undeniable. But... the part of the story that isn't told, at least in “official” circles, is that Byrd and his forces encountered heavy resistance to their Antarctic venture from “flying saucers” and had to call off the mission.

On 5 March, 1947 the “El Mercurio” newspaper of Santiago, Chile, had a headline article “On Board the Mount Olympus on the High Seas” which quoted Byrd in an interview with Lee van Atta:

Adm. Byrd declared today that it was imperative for the United States to initiate immediate defense measures against hostile regions. Furthermore, Byrd stated that he “didn’t want to frighten anyone unduly” but that it was “a bitter reality that in case of a new war the continental United States would be attacked by flying objects which could fly from pole to pole at incredible speeds”.

We have seen evidence on the Giza​ Plateau of scorch marks which are in places where the sun would have been focused onto the ground from the strong reflecting heat of the sun off the polished limestone casing blocks. This lead us to surmise that the bowls gathered at Abu Ghorab, which seem to have been used elsewhere to be brought to Abu Ghorab, could have been placed to reflect the heat of the sun to specific places for heating and cutting blocks, for instance. Just as a solar oven can be moved to be set up in different places. It's a theory that made sense to us so we are sharing it for what it's worth.

node.text:
The Aquatic Ape Theory of human evolution anyone!? Making any connections here?

The most controversial of the accounts is from a book entitled The Sirius Mystery written by Robert Temple in 1971. The Dogon, an ancient African tribe from Mali, knew details about Sirius that they passed on to anthropologists in the 1930s. This knowledge, such as that Sirius is a binary star and has two other stars in its solar system was impossible to know without the use of telescopes. Even then, it was not known by mainstream scientists. The Dogon claimed that they had direct connections with beings from Sirius.

They believed that humanity was born and helped by the Nommo, a race of amphibians who were inhabitants of a planet circling Sirius B.

Specifically, these beings were amphibians that resembled legendary beings we call mermaids.

They are said to have descended from the sky in a vessel accompanied by fire and thunder and imparted profound knowledge to humans.

Interestingly, mermaid type beings were also part of the writings of Atlantis and Vedic texts, where they were known as Telchines and Naggas, respectively. Also, the Sumerians, Egyptians, Israelites, and Babylonians all believed that some sort of "great teacher came and shared their knowledge with us. All cultures have similar stories, but just with different names.
